modules.description: Provides functions to stream data in and out of tar archives, including reading headers, extracting files, and writing entries. Works with byte sequences, file descriptors, and custom data structures for tar entries. Used to process large archives incrementally without loading entire files into memory.

Provides functions to decode, extract, and create tar archives using Lwt_unix for asynchronous I/O. Works with tar headers, file descriptors, and file paths to process archive contents. Extracts archives into directories, creates archives from directories, and appends files with custom headers.

Provides functions to read, write, and manipulate tar archives using Unix file descriptors. Works with tar headers, extended headers, and file descriptors to extract, create, and append files. Enables extracting archives into a directory, creating archives from a directory, and appending individual files with custom headers.
